The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 Davos, Jan. 28: India today pitched for $15-billion foreign investment in 2006-07 to push up growth to over 8 per cent. In the ?India breakfast? meet here, finance minister P. Chidambaram, commerce minister Kamal Nath and Planning Commission deputy chairman Montek Singh Ahluwalia assured potential global investors that New Delhi was committed to reforms. But they made it clear that the money should not replace or displace jobs.

 Mumbai, Jan. 28: United Breweries has approved the scheme of amalgamation of Mangalore Breweries amp; Distilleries and demerger of the brewing business of Associated Breweries amp; Distilleries . It has fixed the appointed date for the scheme on April 1, 2005, the company today informed the stock exchanges. 

 Chennai, Jan. 28: The inclusion of gold in the Multi Commodity Exchange of India was the main reason behind the spurt in the prices of the yellow metal during the past six months, according to Madras Jewellers and Diamond Merchants? Association.




